<subSubSection id="1FD5651DFFFDFFEDF824FA466825E704" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="57703696FFFDFFEDF824FA466825E704" blockId="40.[1967,2557,1276,1698]" lastBlockId="40.[1343,2556,1704,3466]" pageId="40" pageNumber="345">
The geographical proximity of 
<taxonomicName id="90CF4D15FFFDFFEDF6FBFA4666B3E5BC" authorityName="Lorini &amp; Persson" authorityYear="1990" box="[2415,2555,1469,1502]" class="Mammalia" family="Callitrichidae" genus="Leontopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caissara">L. caissara</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="90CF4D15FFFDFFEDF863FA1F67FFE667" authorityName="Mikan" authorityYear="1823" box="[2039,2231,1508,1541]" class="Mammalia" family="Callitrichidae" genus="Leontopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysopygus">L. chrysopygus</taxonomicName>
and the finding that some captive 
<taxonomicName id="90CF4D15FFFDFFEDF7E5F9F46664E64E" authorityName="Mikan" authorityYear="1823" box="[2161,2348,1551,1580]" class="Mammalia" family="Callitrichidae" genus="Leontopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysopygus">L. chrysopygus</taxonomicName>
show a pelage color pattern very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="90CF4D15FFFDFFEDF634F9C868AFE619" authorityName="Lorini &amp; Persson" authorityYear="1990" class="Mammalia" family="Callitrichidae" genus="Leontopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caissara">L. caissara</taxonomicName>
led to the suggestion that 
<taxonomicName id="90CF4D15FFFDFFEDF6F9F9A566B3E619" authorityName="Lorini &amp; Persson" authorityYear="1990" box="[2413,2555,1630,1659]" class="Mammalia" family="Callitrichidae" genus="Leontopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caissara">L. caissara</taxonomicName>
was a subspecies or mere color variant of 
<taxonomicName id="90CF4D15FFFDFFEDFADDF953694AE6AB" authorityName="Mikan" authorityYear="1823" box="[1353,1538,1704,1737]" class="Mammalia" family="Callitrichidae" genus="Leontopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysopygus">L. chrysopygus</taxonomicName>
. This was refuted by an analysis of the cranial and mandibular morphology by C. Burity and coworkers in 1999, which found 
<taxonomicName id="90CF4D15FFFDFFEDF7D0F9346798E692" authorityName="Lorini &amp; Persson" authorityYear="1990" box="[2116,2256,1743,1776]" class="Mammalia" family="Callitrichidae" genus="Leontopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caissara">L. caissara</taxonomicName>
to be distinct. A molecular genetic analysis by B. Perez-Sweeney and coworkers in 2008 confirmed the conclusion of Burity, and placed 
<taxonomicName id="90CF4D15FFFDFFEDF8B2F8D968FCE75D" authorityName="Lorini &amp; Persson" authorityYear="1990" box="[1830,1972,1826,1855]" class="Mammalia" family="Callitrichidae" genus="Leontopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caissara">L. caissara</taxonomicName>
as a sister species to a clade comprising 
<taxonomicName id="90CF4D15FFFDFFEDFADCF8BE6A89E704" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1766" box="[1352,1473,1861,1894]" class="Mammalia" family="Callitrichidae" genus="Leontopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rosalia">L. rosalia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="90CF4D15FFFDFFEDF99CF8BE6989E704" authorityName="Mikan" authorityYear="1823" box="[1544,1729,1861,1894]" class="Mammalia" family="Callitrichidae" genus="Leontopithecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysopygus">L. chrysopygus</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1FD5651DFFFDFFEDFAD3F88E6915E7B9" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" type="multiple">
<caption id="03B0661EFFFDFFEDFAD3F88E6915E7B9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5730844" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5730844" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5730844/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="345" targetBox="[1355,1934,1282,1689]" targetPageId="40">
<paragraph id="57703696FFFDFFEDFAD3F88E6915E7B9" blockId="40.[1343,2556,1704,3466]" pageId="40" pageNumber="345">
<emphasis id="65BBEA84FFFDFFEDFAD3F88E6ABEE7EC" box="[1351,1526,1909,1934]" pageId="40" pageNumber="345">Distribution.</emphasis>
SE 
<collectingCountry id="2FD87606FFFDFFEDF9ACF88E69CEE7EC" box="[1592,1670,1909,1934]" name="Brazil" pageId="40" pageNumber="345">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(states of 
<collectingRegion id="950BF874FFFDFFEDF8B7F88E68CCE7EC" box="[1827,1924,1909,1934]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="40" pageNumber="345">Parana</collectingRegion>
&amp; 
<collectingRegion id="950BF874FFFDFFEDF822F88E6702E7EC" box="[1974,2122,1909,1934]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="40" pageNumber="345">Sao Paulo</collectingRegion>
), on Superagti I, and on the mainland in parts of the valleys of the rios Sebui and dos Patos;its entire distribution is less than 300 km?®.
</paragraph>
